From: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Date: Thu, 5 Oct 2023 21:42:47 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] ext4: add missing initialization of call_notify_error in
 update_super_work()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.6.2
Git-commit: ee6a12d0d4d85f3833d177cd382cd417f0ef011b

[ Upstream commit ee6a12d0d4d85f3833d177cd382cd417f0ef011b ]

Fixes: ff0722de896e ("ext4: add periodic superblock update check")
Signed-off-by: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/ext4/super.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/ext4/super.c b/fs/ext4/super.c
index dbebd8b3..6f48dec1 100644
--- a/fs/ext4/super.c
+++ b/fs/ext4/super.c
@@ -768,7 +768,8 @@ static void update_super_work(struct work_struct *work)
 	 */
 	if (!sb_rdonly(sbi->s_sb) && journal) {
 		struct buffer_head *sbh = sbi->s_sbh;
-		bool call_notify_err;
+		bool call_notify_err = false;
+
 		handle = jbd2_journal_start(journal, 1);
 		if (IS_ERR(handle))
 			goto write_directly;
